metadata.name: OLOKUN HEAD
metadata.description:
it's one of the eighteen copper alloy sculpture that was unearthed in 1938 at ife in nigeria. it is believed to represent a king. it is probably made in the 12th century, although in the yoruba religion Olokun is said to be an Orisha spirit(deity) Goddess of the river

PROPERTIES:
Medium: made of brass bronze head
Height: 35cm
Width: 12.5cm
Depth: 15cm
Weight :5.1kg
